{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013gE9yvRc67HKK1wUFuJBa1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue! Looking at the parse_create_view code:\n\n1. `name = self.parse_object_name(false)?` - parses the view name\n2. Then ClickHouse-specific column parsing\n3. Otherwise: `self.parse_parenthesized_column_list(Optional, false)?` - parses optional column list\n\nFor `MATERIALIZED VIEW FOO COPY GRANTS (A, B) AS SELECT A, B FROM TBL`:\n- Parses `MATERIALIZED`, then `VIEW`\n\n\n- Parses name `FOO`\n- Then tries to parse the column list, but the parentheses come after `COPY GRANTS`, not immediately after the view name. The parser is looking for columns in the wrong position—it expects them right after the name, but the actual SQL has `COPY GRANTS` in between.\n- The parser successfully reads `COPY GRANTS`, but then expects `AS` next. Instead it finds `(A, B)`, which causes the error. The fix is to check for a column list after parsing `COPY GRANTS`, since Snowflake allows columns to appear in that position.\n\nFor the second case with `CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW tbl_1 (col1, col2, ...) AS ...`, I'm wondering why `parse_parenthesized_column_list` fails with \"Expected Table name, found: (\" when it should handle the optional column list after the view name.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1217,"cache_read_input_tokens":99907,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1217},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6db9aadd-b916-4297-8153-a3488ed06c02","uuid":"a8c4615a-ab11-4e83-a75f-e911a035ab98"}
